# CODEOWNERS — review routing for `neo4` (Neo Elastic Network).
#
# Every PR that touches a path below requires review from the listed
# owners. The default catch-all at the bottom ensures every change has
# at least one designated reviewer.
#
# Syntax: <path> <owner>... — see GitHub docs for full pattern rules.

# ─── Smart contracts (L1 + L2) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Changes here are consensus-affecting on any deployed chain. Require
# review from contract-domain owners.
/contracts/                  @r3e-network/contracts-reviewers
/external/foreign-contracts/ @r3e-network/contracts-reviewers

# ─── Cryptographic primitives + on-chain verifier parity ───────────────
# Hash functions, Merkle trees, signature verification, proof-payload
# wire formats. Drift here breaks settlement / fraud-proof / escape-hatch
# flows.
/src/Neo.L2.State/                                @r3e-network/crypto-reviewers
/src/Neo.L2.Proving/                              @r3e-network/crypto-reviewers
/src/Neo.L2.Challenge/                            @r3e-network/crypto-reviewers
/bridge/                                          @r3e-network/crypto-reviewers
/tests/Neo.L2.State.UnitTests/UT_OnChainMerkleVerifyParity.cs  @r3e-network/crypto-reviewers
/tests/Neo.L2.Challenge.UnitTests/UT_RestrictedExecutionFraudVerifierParity.cs  @r3e-network/crypto-reviewers
/tests/Neo.L2.Challenge.UnitTests/UT_GovernanceFraudVerifierParity.cs  @r3e-network/crypto-reviewers
/tests/Neo.L2.Bridge.UnitTests/UT_MpcFraudProof_RealCrypto.cs  @r3e-network/crypto-reviewers

